Of course! Here is a simple, complete, and well-commented website that does exactly that.

You can create these three files in the same folder and open `index.html` in your web browser to see it work.

### 1. `index.html` (The Structure)
This file creates the basic structure of the page: a title, a button, and a place to display the joke.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Random Joke Generator</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>

    <div class="container">
        <h1>Random Joke Generator</h1>
        <button id="jokeButton">Tell Me a Joke!</button>
        <p id="jokeDisplay">Click the button to see a joke!</p>
    </div>

    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

---

### 2. `style.css` (The Design)
This file makes the website look nice and clean. It centers the content, styles the button, and formats the text.

```css
